Note:
P1-E v3 Layer 3 thread-safety test. The orchestrator's
set_active_build_context / get_active_opt_level pair uses a shared
module-global cell per design v3 section 19.6 option 3 (CEO-ratified).
The contract is: every worker in the same build writes the SAME
pointer to the cell, so concurrent writes are idempotent and benign.

This test simulates that workflow in a single-threaded harness by:
  1. Pinning a fake BuildContext.
  2. Pinning it again (simulating a second worker writing the same
     pointer).
  3. Confirming the read returns the configured opt_level.
  4. Re-pinning to 0 (simulating tear-down).
  5. Confirming the read falls back to BUILD_OPT_BASIC.
  6. Re-pinning multiple times in a loop to confirm the cell never
     reaches an undefined state.

Full multi-threaded execution is part of the parallel-compilation
integration harness; this test verifies the per-thread contract holds
in the single-threaded case, which is the foundation the
multi-threaded case builds on. The same cell semantics apply to both.

Exit codes:
  0   = all checks passed
  1-N = check N failed
:End Note

Import "compiler/driver/compile_orchestrator.runa" as CompileOrch

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate two fake BuildContexts, each writing a different
    Note: opt_level so we can confirm the cell tracks whichever pointer
    Note: was written last.
    Let ctx_a be allocate(32)
    If ctx_a is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let ctx_b be allocate(32)
    If ctx_b is equal to 0:
        Return 2
    End If

    Note: ctx_a: opt_level = 2 (BUILD_OPT_STANDARD).
    __store(ctx_a, 0, 0)
    __store(ctx_a, 8, 0)
    __store(ctx_a, 16, 2)
    __store(ctx_a, 24, 0)

    Note: ctx_b: opt_level = 3 (BUILD_OPT_AGGRESSIVE).
    __store(ctx_b, 0, 0)
    __store(ctx_b, 8, 0)
    __store(ctx_b, 16, 3)
    __store(ctx_b, 24, 0)

    Note: Check 3 -- pin ctx_a, read opt_level returns 2.
    proc set_active_build_context from CompileOrch with ctx_a
    Let read_a be proc get_active_opt_level from CompileOrch
    If read_a is not equal to 2:
        Return 3
    End If

    Note: Check 4 -- "worker 2" pins the SAME ctx_a (idempotent write
    Note: case). Read still returns 2.
    proc set_active_build_context from CompileOrch with ctx_a
    Let read_a2 be proc get_active_opt_level from CompileOrch
    If read_a2 is not equal to 2:
        Return 4
    End If

    Note: Check 5 -- switching to ctx_b changes the observed value
    Note: (this is the "different BuildContext per build" scenario;
    Note: within a single build all workers use the same context, but
    Note: across consecutive builds the pinned pointer changes).
    proc set_active_build_context from CompileOrch with ctx_b
    Let read_b be proc get_active_opt_level from CompileOrch
    If read_b is not equal to 3:
        Return 5
    End If

    Note: Check 6 -- pin loop: repeatedly write the same pointer
    Note: confirms the cell never desynchronizes.
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 16:
        proc set_active_build_context from CompileOrch with ctx_b
        Let li be proc get_active_opt_level from CompileOrch
        If li is not equal to 3:
            Return 6
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Check 7 -- re-pin to 0 returns the default fallback.
    proc set_active_build_context from CompileOrch with 0
    Let read_zero be proc get_active_opt_level from CompileOrch
    If read_zero is not equal to 1:
        Return 7
    End If

    Note: Check 8 -- alternating pins across contexts; each read
    Note: tracks the most recent write.
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than 8:
        proc set_active_build_context from CompileOrch with ctx_a
        Let la be proc get_active_opt_level from CompileOrch
        If la is not equal to 2:
            Return 8
        End If
        proc set_active_build_context from CompileOrch with ctx_b
        Let lb be proc get_active_opt_level from CompileOrch
        If lb is not equal to 3:
            Return 8
        End If
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While

    Note: Cleanup: re-pin to 0 before exit so subsequent tests start
    Note: from a clean slate.
    proc set_active_build_context from CompileOrch with 0
    deallocate(ctx_a)
    deallocate(ctx_b)

    Note: All idempotent-write and re-pin checks passed.
    Return 0
End Process
